  "articleSummary": "The articleargues that a truly collaborative culture—likened to “Happy Honey Bees” rather than a “swarm of murder hornets”—is essential for organizations that want to capture breakthrough ideas from any employee, regardless of rank. It presents two core principles: celebrating all ideas (especially the absurd) and welcoming contributions from anyone, illustrated with the story of PepsiCo janitor‑turned‑VP Richard Montañez whose unsolicited pitch generated billions. The piece is written as an instructional, upbeat tutorial aimed at managers and leaders who want to assess and improve their workplace’s openness to ideas, and it previews a follow‑up article on the specific processes and habits that sustain such a culture.",
